<DOC><DOCNO> AP900127-0081 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-01-27-90 1344EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Panama-Arrests     01-27 0192</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Panama-Arrests,0200</SECOND><HEAD>Two Suspects Caught In Killing Of American</HEAD><DATELINE>PANAMA CITY, Panama (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Two people have been arrested in thekilling of the American finance director of the Panama CanalCommission, police announced Saturday.   William Joyce was shot in his home Tuesday by an intruder.   Joyce, 56, was taken to the U.S. military's Gorgas Hospital anddied early Wednesday. The two hooded burglars took money andjewelry from Joyce's home. Police said they had recovered thejewelry.   Joyce was the fourth-highest official of the nine-membercommission, which runs the Panama Canal.   Leslie Loaiza, police director, told reporters Saturday that19-year-old Rafael Palma Ricaurter and an unidentified minor hadbeen arrested in connection with the case.   Loaiza said the minor told authorities he shot Joyce in theabdomen because ``he didn't want to sit down.''   The minor also is wanted by Interpol authorities in neighboringCosta Rica on suspicion of assaulting and killing a Costa Rican lawenforcement agent, Loaiza said.   Following the shooting, the U.S. Southern Command said Thursdaythat it was increasing its military patrols in an effort to check acrime wave sweeping the capital and surrounding areas.</TEXT></DOC>